1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,179 --> 00:01:37,778
=Episode 31=
(Story of Time)

3
00:01:42,648 --> 00:01:43,408
Junhang?

4
00:01:48,488 --> 00:01:49,288
Junhang?

5
00:01:58,768 --> 00:01:59,488
I'm sorry.

6
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:01,648
Junhang, come on.

7
00:02:09,207 --> 00:02:10,088
What...

8
00:02:30,696 --> 00:02:35,128
(Emergency)

9
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:51,800
(Qidaohezi People's Hospital, 1995)

10
00:02:56,964 --> 00:03:01,112
(Rest Cemetery, Qidaohezi, 2004)

11
00:03:08,204 --> 00:03:10,456
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School, 2004)

12
00:03:48,268 --> 00:03:52,632
(Rest Cemetery, 2010)

13
00:04:03,951 --> 00:04:08,344
(Rest Cemetery, 2010)

14
00:04:11,128 --> 00:04:14,408
Mom, I'd been looking
everywhere for you.

15
00:04:15,727 --> 00:04:17,967
So you'd been by my side all along.

16
00:04:21,568 --> 00:04:23,967
Why didn't you come find me?

17
00:04:26,008 --> 00:04:29,887
You know?
I'd been looking for you for so long.

18
00:04:32,048 --> 00:04:34,407
I'd been looking for you all this time.

19
00:04:39,568 --> 00:04:41,488
Why did you abandon me?

20
00:04:44,087 --> 00:04:45,168
Do you know?

21
00:04:46,207 --> 00:04:49,008
I'd rather die with you

22
00:04:50,008 --> 00:04:52,087
than be abandoned by you.

23
00:05:09,267 --> 00:05:11,384
(Rest Cemetery, 2010)

24
00:05:23,248 --> 00:05:27,407
(Why would a cart and shovel
appear here that night?)

25
00:05:35,447 --> 00:05:38,447
(Why is the grass here unusually lush?)

26
00:06:25,008 --> 00:06:28,688
Li Meng, I know where Zhou Na's body is.

27
00:06:34,808 --> 00:06:39,087
(But knowing this won't help you.)

28
00:06:40,527 --> 00:06:45,688
(You'll never find Zhou Na,
nor will you find Xiaoyu.)

29
00:06:51,207 --> 00:06:52,568
Take the body back to the station.

30
00:06:52,568 --> 00:06:53,287
The stone too.

31
00:06:53,287 --> 00:06:54,008
Carry it away.

32
00:06:55,327 --> 00:06:55,928
Captain Li,

33
00:06:56,887 --> 00:06:59,447
this stone was found next to the body.

34
00:06:59,767 --> 00:07:01,447
We need to take it back for examination.

35
00:07:02,608 --> 00:07:04,767
Did you find
any other physical evidence?

36
00:07:05,008 --> 00:07:05,592
No.

37
00:07:05,847 --> 00:07:06,447
And the gun?

38
00:07:07,647 --> 00:07:08,407
Haven't found it.

39
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:09,767
Keep searching.

40
00:07:10,168 --> 00:07:10,767
Understood.

41
00:07:12,847 --> 00:07:13,447
Captain Li,

42
00:07:13,527 --> 00:07:16,688
how did Bai Shu know
that the body was buried right here?

43
00:07:19,327 --> 00:07:21,767
She said
she was at the scene that night.

44
00:07:22,087 --> 00:07:25,168
She saw the cart and shovel
used during the day.

45
00:07:26,207 --> 00:07:29,287
Given Zhang Cuiping's build,
she unlikely moved the body by hand.

46
00:07:29,647 --> 00:07:31,368
So that cart would be her best tool.

47
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:34,368
The cart still being there meant
she hadn't moved the body at all.

48
00:07:34,688 --> 00:07:36,928
Instead, she buried the body
on the spot with the shovel.

49
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:39,207
Bai Shu is so clever.

50
00:07:41,168 --> 00:07:43,168
She topped
the provincial gaokao exam that year.

51
00:07:43,168 --> 00:07:44,168
Could she not be smart?

52
00:07:44,928 --> 00:07:45,816
When we arrived,

53
00:07:45,816 --> 00:07:49,368
we dug ten more centimeters of dirt
before discovering Zhou Na's body.

54
00:07:49,887 --> 00:07:52,928
It proves Bai Shu called the police
before she had dug up the body.

55
00:07:53,287 --> 00:07:54,207
Since she hadn't,

56
00:07:54,488 --> 00:07:57,928
why would she dare call you
to prove her guess was right?

57
00:08:00,327 --> 00:08:02,368
By the way, have you ever fired a gun?

58
00:08:04,048 --> 00:08:06,287
What kind of question is that?
Have I ever fired a gun?

59
00:08:06,368 --> 00:08:07,368
That's my profession.

60
00:08:07,368 --> 00:08:08,287
What do you think?

61
00:08:08,447 --> 00:08:09,527
Have you fired a gun?

62
00:08:10,327 --> 00:08:10,928
Yeah, I have.

63
00:08:12,488 --> 00:08:13,808
She dug up that gun.

64
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:17,287
No.

65
00:08:18,008 --> 00:08:19,008
The gun is in her hands.

66
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:27,488
Hello?

67
00:08:27,527 --> 00:08:28,727
Hello? Bai Shu.

68
00:08:28,727 --> 00:08:29,728
What are you doing?

69
00:08:30,527 --> 00:08:31,847
Let's meet and talk.

70
00:08:32,488 --> 00:08:33,807
I can't. I'm busy now.

71
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:35,407
What keeps you busy?

72
00:08:35,887 --> 00:08:37,008
I can't tell you.

73
00:08:37,448 --> 00:08:38,448
Where are you going?

74
00:08:40,248 --> 00:08:42,767
I'll contact you
after things are settled.

75
00:08:43,488 --> 00:08:44,807
One, two, one.

76
00:08:45,488 --> 00:08:46,567
Hello, Bai Shu?

77
00:08:47,128 --> 00:08:47,767
Bai Shu?

78
00:08:49,407 --> 00:08:51,968
I heard students
doing exercises on the phone.

79
00:08:54,527 --> 00:08:56,008
Didn't we find

80
00:08:56,008 --> 00:08:59,088
Ge Wenjun has a work-assigned apartment
at No. 3 Qianjin Road?

81
00:08:59,567 --> 00:09:01,647
Check if there's a school
near that apartment.

82
00:09:05,608 --> 00:09:07,407
No. 3 Qianjin Road.

83
00:09:09,728 --> 00:09:11,368
Yes, there is a school.

84
00:09:15,128 --> 00:09:15,728
Shun,

85
00:09:16,608 --> 00:09:18,608
I'm sending you an address.
Meet up with us.

86
00:09:19,047 --> 00:09:19,687
Got it.

87
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,088
Grandma, you're so pretty.

88
00:09:23,088 --> 00:09:25,488
You're the prettiest.

89
00:09:26,407 --> 00:09:27,128
There.

90
00:09:29,047 --> 00:09:30,488
Give Mom a call.

91
00:09:30,647 --> 00:09:31,248
Okay.

92
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:38,167
Bai Shu.

93
00:09:39,887 --> 00:09:41,208
(Bai Shu)
It's your mom's name.

94
00:09:41,848 --> 00:09:42,448
(Bai Shu)
Come on.

95
00:09:49,608 --> 00:09:50,328
Speak.

96
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:52,328
Mom, where are you?

97
00:09:52,328 --> 00:09:53,647
Come find us quickly.

98
00:09:54,190 --> 00:09:56,328
(Bai Shu)

99
00:09:56,328 --> 00:09:57,047
Xiaoyu!

100
00:10:12,008 --> 00:10:13,527
ظآزLittle frogظآز

101
00:10:13,927 --> 00:10:15,927
ظآزLoves to singظآز

102
00:10:16,527 --> 00:10:19,968
ظآزCroak, croak, croak croakظآز

103
00:10:20,167 --> 00:10:23,968
ظآزWhat song does it love to singظآز

104
00:10:32,527 --> 00:10:34,208
Shun, did you bring her?

105
00:10:34,488 --> 00:10:36,167
Notified her. She'll be here soon.

106
00:10:42,407 --> 00:10:46,167
Sorry, the subscriber you dialed
is temporarily unavailable.

107
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:49,608
ظآزWhat song does it love to singظآز

108
00:10:56,368 --> 00:10:57,728
ظآزLittle swallowظآز

109
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:04,407
Xiaoyu!

110
00:11:14,527 --> 00:11:15,407
Xiaoyu!

111
00:11:28,488 --> 00:11:30,128
Bai Shu, put the gun down.

112
00:11:30,287 --> 00:11:30,968
No way.

113
00:11:31,807 --> 00:11:32,687
Put the gun down.

114
00:11:33,047 --> 00:11:35,167
She's guilty,
and the law will judge her.

115
00:11:59,608 --> 00:12:00,248
Bai Shu.

116
00:12:00,608 --> 00:12:01,368
Bai Shu.

117
00:12:01,687 --> 00:12:02,488
Bai Shu.

118
00:12:14,968 --> 00:12:15,687
Shoot.

119
00:12:17,887 --> 00:12:20,927
Someone like her
doesn't deserve forgiveness.

120
00:12:22,488 --> 00:12:24,927
She hurt the people who loved you.

121
00:12:27,287 --> 00:12:28,488
Think about Zhang Fang,

122
00:12:29,167 --> 00:12:30,088
Ms. Zhou,

123
00:12:30,848 --> 00:12:31,848
and your mother.

124
00:12:33,887 --> 00:12:34,807
She deserves to die.

125
00:12:35,368 --> 00:12:36,567
Ren Xiaoming, shut up!

126
00:12:37,647 --> 00:12:41,368
I promised I'd stay by your side
no matter what you do.

127
00:12:46,128 --> 00:12:47,088
When you shoot

128
00:12:47,887 --> 00:12:48,887
and Li Meng shoots...

129
00:12:50,848 --> 00:12:55,248
After two gunshots, I'll jump from here.

130
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,488
I'll die with you.

131
00:12:58,687 --> 00:12:59,488
Ren Xiaoming!

132
00:13:00,167 --> 00:13:00,848
Shoot.

133
00:13:01,128 --> 00:13:02,448
- Stay out of this.
- Leave me be.

134
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:03,687
Shoot.

135
00:13:06,807 --> 00:13:08,488
Why did you contact Ren Xiaoming?

136
00:13:09,407 --> 00:13:10,927
You know I hate her the most.

137
00:13:11,368 --> 00:13:13,767
Bai Shu and I
will be best friends for life.

138
00:13:14,248 --> 00:13:16,567
I'll take her anywhere she wants to go.

139
00:13:16,887 --> 00:13:18,887
I'll also help her
find her biological parents.

140
00:13:25,848 --> 00:13:27,047
Ren Xiaoming, stop it.

141
00:13:32,448 --> 00:13:34,128
Her crimes are unforgivable.

142
00:13:39,407 --> 00:13:40,728
Her daughter died.

143
00:13:42,567 --> 00:13:43,328
Gone.

144
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:46,968
That was the person she loved most.

145
00:13:47,887 --> 00:13:49,807
How could she ever move on?

146
00:13:57,807 --> 00:14:00,608
Now you'll know what it feels like
to lose someone dear.

147
00:14:12,047 --> 00:14:14,608
Grandma, I'm coming to find you.

148
00:14:16,968 --> 00:14:18,287
Five.

149
00:14:21,848 --> 00:14:23,167
Four.

150
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:27,368
Three.

151
00:14:29,608 --> 00:14:31,088
Two.

152
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:36,608
One.

153
00:14:52,008 --> 00:14:53,008
Grandma!

154
00:14:55,887 --> 00:14:57,407
I found you.

155
00:14:58,927 --> 00:14:59,687
Good girl.

156
00:15:00,368 --> 00:15:02,047
You're amazing.

157
00:15:14,968 --> 00:15:15,968
You won.

158
00:15:17,248 --> 00:15:17,927
Go to your mom.

159
00:15:18,248 --> 00:15:19,368
- Mom!
- Xiaoyu.

160
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,728
Bye, Grandma.

161
00:15:37,407 --> 00:15:38,968
Bye, sweetheart.

162
00:16:47,128 --> 00:16:48,088
Hello, Xiaofei?

163
00:16:48,608 --> 00:16:50,167
Xiaoming, come back quick.

164
00:16:50,448 --> 00:16:51,807
Mom's sick and hospitalized.

165
00:16:54,328 --> 00:16:56,248
The tumor ruptured,
causing massive bleeding.

166
00:16:57,208 --> 00:17:00,287
If you agree to surgery,
there's a chance to prolong her life.

167
00:17:00,368 --> 00:17:01,927
But that chance is extremely slim.

168
00:17:02,488 --> 00:17:05,367
Most likely,
she won't survive the operation.

169
00:17:05,847 --> 00:17:07,607
Discuss it among yourselves.

170
00:17:07,767 --> 00:17:09,127
If you agree, someone has to sign.

171
00:17:10,087 --> 00:17:11,728
Uncle Li, how should we sign this?

172
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:12,928
I'll sign.

173
00:17:13,488 --> 00:17:14,047
Here.

174
00:17:14,287 --> 00:17:14,888
You...

175
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:17,208
- You are?
- I'm her daughter.

176
00:17:18,574 --> 00:17:19,971
(Surgical Informed Consent Form)

177
00:17:30,168 --> 00:17:31,527
Mom, you're awake.

178
00:17:45,327 --> 00:17:46,488
Have some warm water.

179
00:18:03,087 --> 00:18:06,448
Yuxiu, you're here.

180
00:18:13,327 --> 00:18:15,408
I'm giving Xiaofei back to you.

181
00:18:19,688 --> 00:18:22,527
You two live well together from now on.

182
00:18:28,168 --> 00:18:31,287
The medicine is in the middle drawer
of the cabinet.

183
00:18:32,008 --> 00:18:35,488
Xiaoming always hides it,
afraid Xiaofei will throw it away.

184
00:18:43,127 --> 00:18:44,488
Mom, what are you talking about?

185
00:18:44,888 --> 00:18:46,087
I'm Xiaoming.

186
00:18:55,928 --> 00:18:57,968
What food did you bring me?

187
00:18:59,168 --> 00:19:00,968
Mom, are you feeling unwell somewhere?

188
00:19:02,567 --> 00:19:03,527
I'm hungry.

189
00:19:07,607 --> 00:19:10,767
I made some porridge,
but I'm not sure if it's good.

190
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:14,367
I'm hungry.

191
00:19:30,488 --> 00:19:31,248
Here.

192
00:19:33,367 --> 00:19:34,968
Slow down.

193
00:19:41,968 --> 00:19:42,928
It's good.

194
00:19:44,287 --> 00:19:45,367
Really?

195
00:19:48,847 --> 00:19:49,807
Slow down.

196
00:19:50,888 --> 00:19:52,008
So good.

197
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:05,047
I've never had porridge so good before,
and my daughter made it for me.

198
00:20:07,527 --> 00:20:08,807
Don't overwork yourself.

199
00:20:10,367 --> 00:20:11,448
You've gotten so thin.

200
00:20:13,488 --> 00:20:15,047
Stop worrying so much.

201
00:20:16,688 --> 00:20:19,047
Life is all about finding joy.

202
00:20:20,047 --> 00:20:21,968
Of course, joy comes through hardship.

203
00:20:23,648 --> 00:20:26,408
Heaven, give me all the hardship

204
00:20:26,688 --> 00:20:28,807
and give all the joy to my daughter.

205
00:20:34,968 --> 00:20:36,928
My daughter is so pretty.

206
00:20:38,527 --> 00:20:43,928
Look at these eyebrows,
nose, eyes, and mouth.

207
00:20:48,008 --> 00:20:49,968
How are you so beautiful?

208
00:20:51,688 --> 00:20:52,527
Mom.

209
00:20:53,448 --> 00:20:55,488
So fair and clean.

210
00:20:57,208 --> 00:20:58,408
Xiaoming,

211
00:20:59,847 --> 00:21:01,408
I love you.

212
00:21:07,488 --> 00:21:09,208
Mom, I love you too.

213
00:21:19,928 --> 00:21:24,367
I've kept the same curly hair
for a lifetime.

214
00:21:47,527 --> 00:21:49,968
This is your mother's delivery record
from back then.

215
00:21:52,048 --> 00:21:53,488
(Delivery Record)

216
00:21:53,488 --> 00:21:54,248
(A baby girl.)

217
00:21:54,616 --> 00:21:55,968
(Umbilical cord around the neck.)

218
00:21:55,968 --> 00:21:56,648
(Stillbirth)

219
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:57,888
(She died right after birth.)

220
00:21:59,047 --> 00:22:00,928
(Then how could I possibly
have a brother?)

221
00:22:04,243 --> 00:22:08,920
(Wen Yuxiu)

222
00:22:10,047 --> 00:22:13,327
Can you look up
this person's delivery record for me?

223
00:22:17,592 --> 00:22:21,248
You gave birth to a healthy baby boy,
who is Xiaofei.

224
00:22:47,248 --> 00:22:50,248
Xiaofei only has one mother,
and that's Meiyan.

225
00:22:52,248 --> 00:22:53,208
She always will be.

226
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,208
You are the best sister he could have.

227
00:23:00,888 --> 00:23:05,008
All these years,
you've been using someone else's name

228
00:23:05,127 --> 00:23:06,047
and identity.

229
00:23:06,807 --> 00:23:08,648
You never thought
about being yourself again?

230
00:23:11,527 --> 00:23:14,168
Whether it's Wen Yuxiu or Zhou Yun,

231
00:23:14,928 --> 00:23:18,008
including the years
I spent in the cellar,

232
00:23:18,367 --> 00:23:19,807
that's my real life.

233
00:23:21,888 --> 00:23:23,847
I've always been myself.

234
00:23:27,127 --> 00:23:28,248
What about Xiaofei?

235
00:23:31,567 --> 00:23:33,888
No need to stir up the silt
at the river's bottom.

236
00:23:36,087 --> 00:23:37,168
The water will turn murky.

237
00:23:39,127 --> 00:23:43,807
And the fish living peacefully
will lose their way.

238
00:24:01,585 --> 00:24:06,232
(Friendship Eatery)

239
00:24:08,127 --> 00:24:12,087
(All these years,
I've had a knot in my heart.)

240
00:24:15,047 --> 00:24:17,047
(That day, I really wanted
to tap on the window.)

241
00:24:18,047 --> 00:24:21,847
(If I had actually knocked,
he would have looked up and seen me.)

242
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,448
(Friendship Eatery, Qidaohezi, 2010)

243
00:24:23,448 --> 00:24:27,327
(And maybe none of what happened later
would have occurred.)

244
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:28,590
(Friendship Eatery, Qidaohezi, 2023)

245
00:25:29,445 --> 00:25:33,168
(Friendship Eatery)

246
00:25:33,168 --> 00:25:33,847
Sir.

247
00:25:34,127 --> 00:25:34,807
You're here.

248
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:45,848
(Friendship Forever)

249
00:26:29,087 --> 00:26:30,847
Why isn't the Guo Bao Rou served yet?

250
00:26:34,168 --> 00:26:35,008
Ren Xiaoming.

251
00:26:38,127 --> 00:26:39,287
Don't be sad.

252
00:26:40,208 --> 00:26:44,248
Even if we had met that day,
I still would have gone out.

253
00:26:45,208 --> 00:26:46,567
The bus was full of kids.

254
00:26:46,807 --> 00:26:48,127
You'd have done the same.

255
00:26:53,248 --> 00:26:54,527
Can you forgive me?

256
00:27:01,648 --> 00:27:02,408
This is for you.

257
00:27:06,767 --> 00:27:08,488
Do you know about my 'dare'?

258
00:27:12,248 --> 00:27:13,248
Ren Xiaoming,

259
00:27:15,688 --> 00:27:17,168
I love...

260
00:27:17,807 --> 00:27:19,287
I love...

261
00:27:27,688 --> 00:27:29,888
Ren Xiaoming!

262
00:27:56,312 --> 00:27:58,577
(Several months later)

263
00:27:59,928 --> 00:28:00,847
Hold this for me.

264
00:28:01,127 --> 00:28:01,928
- Put it in there.
- Okay.

265
00:28:01,928 --> 00:28:03,087
We'll take it out later.

266
00:28:07,408 --> 00:28:08,127
What's wrong?

267
00:28:10,968 --> 00:28:12,408
Sorry, miss, my hand slipped.

268
00:28:12,807 --> 00:28:13,408
It's fine.

269
00:28:13,807 --> 00:28:14,488
I'll handle it.

270
00:28:14,488 --> 00:28:15,208
- Sorry.
- Just go.

271
00:28:15,248 --> 00:28:15,928
It's okay.

272
00:28:37,168 --> 00:28:39,087
(This? It's been ages.)

273
00:28:39,488 --> 00:28:40,648
(Got it from a foreigner.)

274
00:28:40,847 --> 00:28:41,847
(It's from before 1949.)

275
00:29:01,648 --> 00:29:02,648
(Dear Betty,)

276
00:29:03,728 --> 00:29:09,448
(this letter may never reach you.)

277
00:29:11,367 --> 00:29:12,807
(My true identity was discovered.)

278
00:29:12,807 --> 00:29:13,888
(I'm not afraid of death.)

279
00:29:13,888 --> 00:29:16,807
(Death will bring me back to you,)

280
00:29:16,928 --> 00:29:19,928
(back to our hometown,)

281
00:29:20,767 --> 00:29:22,488
(the place where we first met.)

282
00:29:23,008 --> 00:29:24,448
(Betty,)

283
00:29:25,408 --> 00:29:29,728
(I will die young,
but I have no regrets.)

284
00:29:30,367 --> 00:29:33,248
(Because I deeply loved
a beautiful girl.)

285
00:29:34,408 --> 00:29:36,488
(She is the smartest,)

286
00:29:36,488 --> 00:29:38,807
(kindest, and most adorable girl
in the world.)

287
00:29:40,248 --> 00:29:41,888
(You must live well)

288
00:29:42,448 --> 00:29:44,008
(and live happily.)

289
00:29:44,888 --> 00:29:48,168
(May all the beauty in this world
follow you like a shadow.)

290
00:29:50,688 --> 00:29:51,767
(It's a pity)

291
00:29:52,488 --> 00:29:53,728
(that we had no children.)

292
00:29:54,448 --> 00:29:59,248
(But I hope you will in the future.
Whether boy or girl,)

293
00:29:59,248 --> 00:30:01,287
(I will love them sincerely.)

294
00:30:01,968 --> 00:30:03,448
(Because they are yours.)

295
00:30:05,928 --> 00:30:08,728
(I know they will love you deeply too.)

296
00:30:09,567 --> 00:30:11,008
(That puts my mind at ease.)

297
00:30:12,127 --> 00:30:13,728
(You'll be a good mother.)

298
00:30:16,448 --> 00:30:17,287
(I love you,)

299
00:30:18,287 --> 00:30:19,208
(in life)

300
00:30:19,688 --> 00:30:20,488
(or death.)

301
00:30:21,488 --> 00:30:23,047
(I love you a thousand times over.)

302
00:30:48,888 --> 00:30:50,405
(La City Express)

303
00:32:02,348 --> 00:32:05,336
(Several years later)

304
00:32:10,527 --> 00:32:12,287
I see the craters on the moon.

305
00:32:17,408 --> 00:32:18,648
And there's a rabbit.

306
00:32:19,728 --> 00:32:20,688
Really?

307
00:32:21,287 --> 00:32:22,248
Let me see.

308
00:32:27,008 --> 00:32:28,327
I see the little rabbit.

309
00:32:28,888 --> 00:32:29,928
Really?

310
00:32:35,928 --> 00:32:37,008
Where?

311
00:32:37,928 --> 00:32:39,087
You actually believed me.

312
00:32:40,287 --> 00:32:42,607
Where is it? I don't see it.

313
00:32:44,448 --> 00:32:45,728
You're so easy to fool.

314
00:32:50,928 --> 00:32:53,047
This thing isn't cheap, is it?

315
00:32:53,287 --> 00:32:54,087
Of course not.

316
00:32:54,567 --> 00:32:56,008
I don't let just anyone touch it.

317
00:33:03,728 --> 00:33:04,367
Xiaoming,

318
00:33:07,408 --> 00:33:08,087
I'm sorry.

319
00:33:08,968 --> 00:33:10,408
Why are you suddenly apologizing?

320
00:33:12,127 --> 00:33:13,688
If not for me that day,

321
00:33:14,448 --> 00:33:16,968
you and He Yuqiong would have met.

322
00:33:17,847 --> 00:33:18,488
And maybe...

323
00:33:18,488 --> 00:33:19,367
Don't say that.

324
00:33:22,287 --> 00:33:24,248
All of this was my own choice.

325
00:33:24,928 --> 00:33:26,047
It's none of your business.

326
00:33:27,008 --> 00:33:28,367
It was a bus full of kids.

327
00:33:28,888 --> 00:33:30,607
You'd have gone too.

328
00:33:36,847 --> 00:33:39,567
You must have missed him a lot
over the years.

329
00:33:42,607 --> 00:33:43,448
Yes, I have.

330
00:33:45,287 --> 00:33:47,367
Well, do you know what my name means?

331
00:33:47,888 --> 00:33:48,488
I don't know.

332
00:33:49,648 --> 00:33:51,367
'Yuqiong' means 'sky.'

333
00:33:51,888 --> 00:33:53,208
So my nickname is Tiantian.

334
00:33:55,607 --> 00:33:58,008
With my name,
all the stars in the sky are yours.

335
00:33:58,888 --> 00:34:00,728
'Yuqiong' means 'sky.'

336
00:34:02,408 --> 00:34:03,847
The sky is always there.

337
00:34:46,647 --> 00:34:50,047
After June,
Venus will rise before the sun.

338
00:34:50,047 --> 00:34:51,087
So it's Morning Star.

339
00:34:51,687 --> 00:34:52,968
If there's anything to regret,

340
00:34:53,207 --> 00:34:55,888
seeing the Morning Star
rise on the horizon

341
00:34:56,087 --> 00:34:57,328
means you can start over.

342
00:35:09,375 --> 00:35:11,512
(He Yuqiong:
Xiaoming, I miss you so much.)

343
00:35:20,344 --> 00:35:21,400
(I miss you too.)

344
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:23,832
(I heard you're back.)

345
00:35:32,967 --> 00:35:34,840
(Come over for a meal.)

346
00:36:00,008 --> 00:36:02,647
You don't need to send me
living expenses monthly anymore.

347
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:04,727
I'm feeling better now.

348
00:36:05,288 --> 00:36:07,127
The community takes good care of me.

349
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:20,629
ظآزSpring flowers bloom,
autumn wind blowsظآز

350
00:37:21,408 --> 00:37:24,087
Ren Xiaoming, you are the best.

351
00:37:24,448 --> 00:37:26,087
Go and do what you want to do.

352
00:37:26,687 --> 00:37:27,968
You have to be happy and joyful.

353
00:37:27,968 --> 00:37:29,127
Enjoy life.

354
00:37:31,888 --> 00:37:34,288
Bai Shu, you're really amazing.

355
00:37:34,368 --> 00:37:35,647
You are very brave.

356
00:37:36,207 --> 00:37:39,087
You must continue to fulfill your dream
of traveling the world.

357
00:37:39,408 --> 00:37:40,207
Keep it up.

358
00:37:40,408 --> 00:37:41,448
Ren Xiaoming.

359
00:37:41,647 --> 00:37:42,687
Bai Shu.

360
00:37:42,848 --> 00:37:46,768
We'll achieve our dream
of traveling the world together.

361
00:37:47,167 --> 00:37:48,727
We'll see every corner of the world.

362
00:37:48,727 --> 00:37:50,687
And we must not forget
each other's promises.

363
00:37:50,888 --> 00:37:52,047
Don't forget the pen.

364
00:37:52,607 --> 00:37:53,888
When someone needs courage,

365
00:37:54,127 --> 00:37:57,607
take out this pen.

366
00:37:57,968 --> 00:37:59,607
We must never betray each other.

367
00:37:59,768 --> 00:38:01,127
We must trust each other.

368
00:38:01,127 --> 00:38:04,647
We'll be together forever and ever.

369
00:38:12,572 --> 00:38:15,547
ظآزYellowed photos, ancient lettersظآز

370
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:19,288
ظآزAnd faded Christmas cardsظآز

371
00:38:19,299 --> 00:38:22,392
ظآزSongs written for you in youthظآز

372
00:38:22,392 --> 00:38:25,426
ظآزYou probably forgot long agoظآز

373
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:28,728
ظآزPast promises are likeظآز

374
00:38:28,728 --> 00:38:32,773
ظآزThe colorful bookmarks in textbooksظآز

375
00:38:33,049 --> 00:38:36,200
ظآزMarking so many beautiful thingsظآز

376
00:38:37,328 --> 00:38:38,488
Xiaoming,

377
00:38:39,127 --> 00:38:40,288
Xiaofei,

378
00:38:40,888 --> 00:38:42,687
take good care of yourselves.

379
00:38:43,704 --> 00:38:46,093
ظآزChanged two peopleظآز

380
00:38:48,368 --> 00:38:49,768
Well, is it romantic?

381
00:38:50,448 --> 00:38:51,408
What is happiness?

382
00:38:51,567 --> 00:38:52,848
This is happiness.

383
00:38:55,888 --> 00:38:58,888
Happy Spring Festival!

384
00:39:07,353 --> 00:39:10,648
ظآزThe distant journey, yesterday's dreamظآز

385
00:39:10,679 --> 00:39:13,304
ظآزAnd the laughter that has faded awayظآز

386
00:39:14,405 --> 00:39:16,195
ظآزMeeting againظآز

387
00:39:16,195 --> 00:39:20,120
ظآزHow many more roads have we traveledظآز

388
00:39:21,450 --> 00:39:24,408
ظآزNo longer the familiar old meظآز

389
00:39:24,537 --> 00:39:27,238
ظآزWith past enthusiastic dreamsظآز

390
00:39:28,169 --> 00:39:31,242
ظآزNot the familiar old youظآز

391
00:39:31,443 --> 00:39:34,580
ظآزWith a still familiar smileظآز

392
00:39:34,926 --> 00:39:38,520
ظآزThe flowing water
takes away the stories of timeظآز

393
00:39:38,572 --> 00:39:41,183
ظآزAnd has changed usظآز

394
00:39:41,693 --> 00:39:45,368
ظآزIn that sentimental and first timeظآز

395
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:48,348
ظآزRecalling the youthظآز

396
